@Lynn 
I get the salt water simmering in the double boiler top, while the bottom also has water heating (at a level that will not allow contact once the top section is in place.)
Then i stir constantly as I add the grits in very small amounts--sort of sprinkledover the surface of the water.  You want to be sure the grits do not clump up, so you continue to stir and sprinkle until all the grits have been added to the water. Then I lift the top section into place and put on the lid, setting a timer for 15 minutes.  Stir a couple of times.  If you want cheese grits, add a tbsp of butter and grated cheese (we like sharp+ Tillamook, but I do not always want cheese grits....)  with the dbl boiler you don't worry about sticking or scorching.
